Ask HN: How are you investing in AI?
text:
It seems clear that we’re on the edge of a rapidly expanding bubble. There will likely be some big winners in the AI space.

This bubble seems different though, as AI seems to be poised to augment capabilities of existing companies vs generating another Google or Tesla.

Where to invest then? Will AI just make bigger companies bigger or are there clear opportunities for startups or smaller companies to rapidly grow?

Any unicorns or will all the benefits be realized at FAANG level companies?
